<section id="architecture">
  <div class="sh"><div class="sh-n">02</div><div class="sh-t">How it works — one Worker, all your destinations</div></div>
  <div class="arch-wrap">
    <div class="arch-grid">
      <div class="arch-l">
        <h2 class="arch-h">Your Cloudflare<br />account. Your<br /><em>credentials. Your data.</em></h2>
        <p class="arch-p">Attestrack is a Cloudflare Worker that runs in your account. You deploy it once. It proxies tracking events server-side to Meta, Google, TikTok, Microsoft, and any analytics destination you configure. Your ad network credentials live in your Worker environment variables — they never touch Attestrack’s infrastructure because there is no Attestrack infrastructure to touch.</p>
        <p class="arch-p">The browser-side adapters initialize pixels after consent and send conversion events to your Worker endpoint — which is on your own domain. First-party. Not blocked. Then the Worker forwards those events to each configured destination simultaneously, server-side, with any additional data enrichment you’ve configured.</p>
        <p class="arch-p"><strong>Nothing goes to Attestrack servers.</strong> There are no Attestrack servers in the tracking data path. It’s your Cloudflare account, your Worker, your event data. The GitHub repo is the product.</p>
        <ul class="flow">
          <li class="flow-item"><div class="flow-n">01</div><div class="flow-body"><strong>Browser fires event to your domain.</strong> <code>/t/event</code> on your own subdomain. First-party request. Not blocked by any ad blocker.</div></li>
          <li class="flow-item"><div class="flow-n">02</div><div class="flow-body"><strong>consent.js verifies consent state.</strong> If consent granted for the relevant category, the event is forwarded to the Worker. If not, it’s logged as a non-consented event in your ClickHouse only.</div></li>
          <li class="flow-item"><div class="flow-n">03</div><div class="flow-body"><strong>Worker enriches and fans out.</strong> Adds hashed PII matching fields, reads your configured strategies, and executes all destinations in parallel via <code>Promise.all</code>.</div></li>
          <li class="flow-item"><div class="flow-n">04</div><div class="flow-body"><strong>ClickHouse gets everything.</strong> Every event — consented or not — goes to your ClickHouse with consent state as a field. Your analytics are complete. Your ad platforms only get consented events.</div></li>
          <li class="flow-item"><div class="flow-n">05</div><div class="flow-body"><strong>Worker returns 200 immediately.</strong> Strategy execution happens in <code>ctx.waitUntil</code>. Zero latency impact on your pages. The browser never waits for ad network responses.</div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="arch-r">
        <div class="code">
          <div class="code-label">wrangler.toml — your configuration</div>
          <pre set:html={`<span class="cd"># Deploy to your Cloudflare account
# npx wrangler deploy</span>

name = <span class="cg">"my-tracking-worker"</span>
main = <span class="cg">"worker/index.js"</span>

[vars]
  SITE_ID = <span class="cg">"your-site"</span>

<span class="cd"># Ad network credentials — yours only
# Never sent anywhere except the ad network</span>
[secrets]
  META_PIXEL_ID        = <span class="co">"..."</span>
  META_ACCESS_TOKEN    = <span class="co">"..."</span>
  GA4_MEASUREMENT_ID   = <span class="co">"..."</span>
  GA4_API_SECRET       = <span class="co">"..."</span>
  TIKTOK_PIXEL_ID      = <span class="co">"..."</span>
  TIKTOK_ACCESS_TOKEN  = <span class="co">"..."</span>
  CLICKHOUSE_URL       = <span class="co">"..."</span>
  CLICKHOUSE_PASSWORD  = <span class="co">"..."</span>

<span class="cd"># Optional: add Attestrue proof layer
# One line. No code changes. No redeployment.</span>
<span class="cd"># LICENSE_KEY = "&lt;your-license-key&gt;"</span>`} />
        </div>
        <div class="code" style="margin-top:12px">
          <div class="code-label">Strategy registration — add any destination</div>
          <pre set:html={`<span class="cd">// packages/strategies/src/index.ts</span>
<span class="cd">// Add your own — same interface</span>

<span class="cb">export const</span> <span class="co">BUNDLED_STRATEGIES</span> = [
  <span class="cg">new MetaStrategy</span>(),
  <span class="cg">new GoogleStrategy</span>(),
  <span class="cg">new TikTokStrategy</span>(),
  <span class="cg">new MicrosoftStrategy</span>(),
  <span class="cg">new ClickHouseStrategy</span>(),
  <span class="cg">new TinybirdStrategy</span>(),
  <span class="cd">// Community strategies:</span>
  <span class="cd">// new SnowflakeStrategy()</span>
  <span class="cd">// new BigQueryStrategy()</span>
  <span class="cd">// new AmplitudeStrategy()</span>
  <span class="cd">// new MixpanelStrategy()</span>
];

<span class="cd">// Implement Strategy interface:
// execute(event, config, env): Promise&lt;Result&gt;
// shouldExecute(event, consentState): boolean
// category(): StrategyCategory</span>`} />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

